  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bc1.",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The vote on second reading passed.",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The vote on the second reading of the 2022 interim budget was held in Parliament today, with 120 votes in favor and 5 votes against. Meanwhile, the interim measure proposed by President Ranil Wickremesinghe was passed with 115 more votes.",
        "While the main opposition United People's Shakti, Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna's 13-member parliament members Professor G. L. Peiris and Dulas Alagaperuma and the Tamil National Federation abstained from voting, the People's Liberation Front and the All Sri Lanka Congress voted against Tamil."
      ],
